    "answer_id" : 1379169,
    "question_id" : 1378798,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>I'm guessing that Java code treats the DVD as a regular file on the filesystem, while Windows probably optimizes read/write. </p>\n\n<p>Since the Java IO calls go to the native/OS calls, I'm guessing that the linux OS is smarter when making the IO calls to read the DVD.</p>\n"
